parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the coil spring perch can cause the coil spring to detach from the vehicle, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The coil spring detaches from the vehicle
the vehicle begins to make a loud noise
the wheel well rubs against the tire
the vehicle becomes difficult to steer
the vehicle collapses onto the tire
and the wheel well scores deep gashes in the tire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the coil spring can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The coil spring cracks or breaks
the vehicle rides rough
the steering wheel vibrates hard
the frame well is broken
and the vehicle becomes difficult to steer.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rust Corrosion on Coil Spring Perch
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Rust corrosion on the coil spring perch can cause the coil spring perch to fail, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Rust is noticed on the coil spring perch
the coil spring perch cracks or breaks
and the coil spring detaches from the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of front axle components can cause loss of control, leading to accidents, and potentially result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Loud popping or grinding noise near the front passenger side of the vehicle
metal hanging from under the vehicle
vehicle instability or loss of control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the automatic transmission can cause the vehicle to become stuck in gear, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potentially result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Transmission gets stuck in gear
hesitation or difficulty shifting gears
unusual noises or vibrations from the transmission.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Gas Tank Pressure Sensor and Return Line Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the gas tank pressure sensor and return lines can cause loss of tank pressure, leakage, and/or improper emission system sensor readouts, leading to poor gas mileage, safety risks, and potential environmental hazards.
symptoms: "Check engine" light comes on
improper functioning of the fuel evaporation system
loss of tank pressure
leakage
and/or improper emission system sensor readouts.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The collapse of the gas tank can cause fuel leakage, fire hazards, and accidents, posing a significant safety risk to drivers and passengers.
symptoms: The gas tank collapses or becomes deformed
"check engine" light comes on
improper functioning of the fuel evaporation system.
